          1.the id of the div shows the date of event. so all photos and captions pertaining to july
          25th would go into a div with the id 25th and so on.

          2. using jquery I have implemented paging so at a particular time only the div of
          a particular day will be visible.

          3. class 'shown' represents that this div is the one that will be seen by
          the user. and similarly the 'hidden' class hides that particular div from the user. hence since 25th
          is the first day hence its corresponding div will have initial class as shown and the rest od the
          div's have class hidden.

          4. in order to remove or add pages just create a div with the above mentioned structure and put the div id
          with a preceeding # into an array called 'dates' in the order in which they have to be shown.

          eg: dates = Array('#25th','#26th','#27th') and so on.if you change the order of the divs in the array then the
          paging order would also get shuffled.

          eg: dates = Array('#25th','#27th','#26th') . the configuration of dates array mentioned here will show the details
          of 27th before 26th
